This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification and segmentation. The use of kernel density matching and geometric transformations also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the mention of brain segmentation across different MRI modalities may indicate a connection to neural engineering (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
